reports/naca0012_airfoil/fix_plan_packet.md:59:Why this is one global `dir3` candidate instead of a local LE-only patch: the measured defect is LE-localized, but the six-block C-grid shares the same wall-normal subdivision across internal block interfaces. Changing only one or two blocks would break shared-face conformity. This candidate therefore applies one consistent `dir3` retune across all six blocks while still targeting the LE buffer-band defect.
